'''North Carolina Highway 114''' is a primary [[state highway]] in the [[U.S. state]] of [[North Carolina]].  It runs from [[Interstate 40 in North Carolina|I-40]] to downtown  [[Drexel, North Carolina|Drexel]].

==Route description==
'''NC 114''' is a spur route, starting at [[Interstate 40 in North Carolina|I-40]] (exit 107), it goes north, crossing [[U.S. Route 70 in North Carolina|US 70]] before entering the town of [[Drexel, North Carolina|Drexel]].  The road ends, after the railroad tracks next to a factory, at Oakland Avenue.  

==Junction list==
The entire route is in [[Burke County, North Carolina|Burke County]].
