==History==
'''NC 114''' was established in 1930 as a new primary route between [[U.S. Route 70 in North Carolina|US 70]]/[[North Carolina Highway 10|NC 10]] to [[Drexel, North Carolina|Drexel]].  In 1977, NC 114 was extended south to its current southern terminus at [[Interstate 40 in North Carolina|I-40]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://members.cox.net/ncroads/nc114.html|title=NCRoads.com: N.C. 114|accessdate=2011-01-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.state-ends.com/ncends/state/114.html|title=NC State Hwy 114 Ends|accessdate=2011-01-06}}</ref>

==Alternate names==
Though the highway is commonly known as "NC 114" throughout the state, the highway does have other known names it uses locally in areas.

*Drexel Road - Road name of entire highway, except in Drexel.
*Main Street - Road name in Drexel.

